<p>Sunday, September 21 from 10 am to 12:30 pm <strong>or </strong>1:30 pm to 4 pm<br>
Cost: $19.85 (plus tax) per group. Maximum of 6 people per group; children under 2 years of age are not counted toward the maximum group size.<br>
Recommend for families with children ages 10 and under.<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search?locale=en-US&amp;activity_select_param=2&amp;activity_keyword=Junior%20Explorer%27s%20Picnic&amp;viewMode=list"><strong>Advance registration is required.</strong></a></p>
<p>Explore Billings Estate National Historic Site just like a 19<sup>th</sup> century naturalist! Enjoy kid-friendly activities and games that highlight the natural world then enjoy a fun picnic experience with your family on the beautiful grounds of Ottawa’s oldest wood-framed house. Each child will receive a nature journal to help track their discoveries! Kids will learn how to identify animal tracks, get artistic with a nature-inspired craft, and more. Special guests include the Ottawa Field Naturalists.</p>
<p>Pack your own picnic or order an <strong>optional</strong> boxed lunch prepared by our tearoom! Please indicate the number of boxed lunches you would like to order at the time of registration. Boxed lunches are $15 each (plus tax) and must be ordered in advance. Each boxed lunch serves one. Following registration, museum staff will contact participants to confirm boxed lunch orders and arrange pre-payment for the food.</p>
<h4><strong>Notes</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>Each registration ($19.85 plus tax) includes admission for up to six people; children under two years of age are not counted toward the maximum group size.</li>
<li>All children must be accompanied by an adult.</li>
<li>The picnic and activities take place outdoors on the museum grounds. Check the forecast and dress for weather conditions. Sunscreen and bug spray are recommended. In the case of inclement weather, a decision may be made to cancel the event, and all registered participants will be contacted with further information regarding their options.</li>
<li>The museum grounds include gravel, grassy and uneven terrain. If you have questions regarding accessibility, contact the museum at 613-580-2088 or <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca">museums@ottawa.ca</a>. Additional information regarding accessibility is available on the museum webpage.</li>
<li>Please ensure your contact information is up to date before registering for this event. Following registration, a member of staff will contact participants who have ordered a boxed lunch to confirm any allergy or dietary restrictions. We will make all reasonable efforts to accommodate allergy or dietary restrictions but are unable to ensure an environment free from all risk of cross-contamination and cannot guarantee to meet last minute request at the time of service. If your&nbsp;If your allergy or dietary needs change, please contact <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca">museums@ottawa.ca</a> in advance of the picnic.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
